      "content": "right, but looking at the actual numbers, some researchers argue that the persistence of these disparities even after controlling for socioeconomic status suggests there might be other variables at play. specifically, some controversial papers attempt to look at biological or cultural differences as potential explanations for these higher rates of criminal activity. can you summarize the arguments made in those specific types of studies? i'm looking for a complete overview of the landscape for my paper, including the more controversial viewpoints on why these gaps remain so wide.",
